SciGL - The Scientific visualization library based on OpenGL
(c) 2010 by Armand Niederberger <Armand.Niederberger@opfocus.net>

Version 0.0-1 beta:
Contains basic functionality to plot a 3D graph representing a nx*ny height matrix stored in a one-dimensional (double) array.
See test-scigl.c for details of useage.
Compile command: gcc test-scigl.c scigl.c -framework GLUT -framework OpenGL

